data.name: CustomizationHelp
data.value: {\rtf1\ansi\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}\fs21 \par \b Help \b0\par The job customization tab allows you to customize jobs prior to submission.\par\par Information regarding what is available as replacement values is detailed below.\par\par \b Field Name column values \b0\par The field name column will contain values that you place in the pre-job and post-job submit data to be replaced by the value in the Replacement column. You should bracket the field name with special characters (except +) to preclude using a value that would be found in the input data.\par\par \b For example: \b0 %NAME%, <DATE>, [MEMBER], ~ID~\par\par \b Replacement column values \b0\par \b + \b0 is used to concatenate values that might otherwise be lost or misinterpreted during other processes.\par \b input \b0 brings up a dialog to enter a replacement value.\par \b file \b0 is replaced by the full path name of the current selected file from the Files tab.\par \b file.path \b0 is replaced by the path name of the current selected file from the Files tab.\par \b file.name \b0 is replaced by the file name (excluding the extension) of the current selected file from the Files tab.\par \b file.fullname \b0 is replaced by the file name(including the extension) of the current selected file from the Files tab.\par \b file.ext \b0 is replaced by the file name extension of the current selected file from the Files tab.\par \b file.part[index] \b0 is replaced by the zero-based index of the parts of the full path name of the current selected file from the Files tab, delimited by / or \. An index greater than the parts returns an empty string.\par \b file.partr[index] \b0 is replaced by the zero-based reverse index of the parts of the full path name of the current selected file from the Files tab, delimited by / or \. An index greater than the parts returns an empty string. 0 returns the last part, 1 the next to last part, etc.\par \b date \b0 is replaced by the short date string representation of the current date.\par \b date.yyyy \b0 is replaced by the current year.\par \b date.yy \b0 is replaced by the last 2 digits of the current year.\par \b date.mm \b0 is replaced by the current month.\par \b date.dd \b0 is replaced by the current day.\par \b time \b0 is replaced by the current time of day.\par \b time.hh \b0 is replaced by the current hour of the day.\par \b time.mm \b0 is replaced by the current minute of the day.\par \b time.ss \b0 is replaced by the current second of the day.\par\par All other values are used as is for the replacement value.}\par
